WorldStage Newsonline– The Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) has described the late Mallam Adamu Ciroma, its Governor from September 24, 1975 to June 28 1977 as a firm believer in the sanctity and independence of the apex bank Ciroma who died on July 5, 2018 was born on November 20 1934 in Potiskum, Yobe State. In a condolence message, the CBN said until his demise, Mallam Ciroma was still of immense service to the Bank. “While we mourn the loss of a very good man, an astute central banker and a patriot, we also celebrate his remarkable life and contribution to the banking industry in Nigeria,” it said. “We pray Almighty Allah to grant his family and the nation the fortitude to bear the irreparable loss.”